<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-293-707  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 293 707.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Jan 31 1989 v3 n5 p33(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Database connection san SQL. (Odesta Corp.'s Helix VMX)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Crabb, Don.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Odesta Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Helix VMX (Computer program) (usage)DEC VAX (Minicomputer).andO;Topic:     Information Storage and RetrievalStructured Query LanguageData Bases.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Database connection sans SQLandM;SQL is not the only way for your Mac to access databases on larger computers.andO;Several Macintosh database vendors have already released products that allowhost computers to function as repositories of Macintosh data.andP;  The Macintoshvendor with the most experience with this kind of system is Odesta Corp.andM;Odesta produces the Helix series of products, including Multiuser Helix andDouble Helix II.andP;  Odesta's Mac-to-VAX database program is Helix VMX.andM;The program allows Double Helix II applications to run on VAX computers underthe VMS operating system.andP;  Helix VMX applications can be run from eitherMacintoshes or VT-series terminals connected to the VAX.andP;  This flexibilityhelps keep equipment costs down because you don't have to buy a Mac for everyHelix VMX user.andM;The difference between an application like Helix VMX and an SQLimplementation on the Mac is that the Helix solution is a closed application.andO;That is, the Helix application works because the data are created usingHelix, stored on a VAX running Helix VMX and accessed by another Helixapplication.andM;Helix VMX is not command-driven the way SQL is.andP;  Helix does not even providean access and specification &quot;language.&quot;andP;  Instead, Helix VMX applications arebuilt by manipulating a number of icons that represent data, calculations,comparisons, selections and so on.andP;  These icons work like SQL's commandlanguage, coupled with the kind of 4GL features that products like Ingresprovide.andM;The Helix method is especially intuitive for users who may not have anyformal training in database structure or rudimentary programming but who knowconceptually what they want to do.andO;</TEXT></DOC>